250 g Ground Beef
¼ cup Basil Pesto
350 g Gnocchi
56 g Baby Spinach
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
56 mL Cream
113 g Baby Tomatoes
0.06 tsp Salt*
0.06 tsp Pepper*
½ tbsp Oil*
2 tbsp Unsalted Butter*

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When the pan is hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then beef.
Cook, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Transfer beef to a plate. Set aside.

Meanwhile, halve baby tomatoes.

Reheat the same pan over medium-high.
When the pan is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, then swirl until melted. Add gnocchi.
Cook, turning occasionally, until golden, 5-6 min.

Add beef, spinach, pesto, tomatoes, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter and cream to the pan with gnocchi.
Cook, stirring often, until spinach wilts and gnocchi is coated, 1-2 min.
Divide gnocchi between plates.
Sprinkle Parmesan over top.

If you've opted to get beef, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the sausage.**